    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURES IN DEPTH -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Features in depth</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Every major <span class="accent">Wordtune feature</span>, tested.</h2>
      <p>What's actually in the box — and how each piece performs when you put it to work on real writing tasks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>AI rewriting with tone modes</h4>
              <p>Highlight any sentence and Wordtune generates alternatives in Casual, Formal, Shorten, or Expand modes. The Casual and Formal modes work well for adjusting email and LinkedIn content tone. Shorten is the most reliable — Expand sometimes adds filler.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Spices — examples, analogies, and cited facts</h4>
              <p>One of the most original features in the category. Position your cursor and Wordtune suggests a statistical fact, analogy, or example relevant to the surrounding context, with a hyperlinked source for verification. Useful for adding evidence mid-draft.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Wordtune Read</h4>
              <p>Upload a PDF or paste a URL and Wordtune condenses it into a scannable summary with citations linking back to the source. Handles documents up to 500 pages. One of the more polished long-document summarizers available at this price point.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Browser extension and Smart Paste</h4>
              <p>The Chrome extension drops Wordtune directly into Gmail, Google Docs, LinkedIn, Slack, Outlook, and Microsoft Word. Smart Paste automatically reformats pasted text for the destination platform — handy when moving content between contexts.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Grammar and spelling checks</h4>
              <p>Available on all plans including free. Works, but underperforms Grammarly on error detection accuracy. Fine for quick catches — not reliable enough to replace a dedicated grammar tool for professional documents.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">06</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Knowledge Library</h4>
              <p>Stores your saved summaries and reading notes with source links. Useful if you're doing ongoing research in a topic area and want to build a personal reference library inside Wordtune.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">07</span>
            <div>
              <h4>What's missing</h4>
              <p>SEO of any kind, paragraph-level rewriting, original content generation from scratch, publishing to any platform, plagiarism checking, active product development, and English output for non-English input languages.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRICING -->
  <section class="cost-section">
    <div class="cost-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Pricing</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Wordtune <span class="accent">actually costs.</span></h2>
      <p>Four tiers from free to custom. The annual plan is where the real value is — $6.99/month for Unlimited is reasonable for what the tool does.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cost-table">
      <div class="cost-row head">
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Tier</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Wordtune</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Best fit</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell brand">theStacc equivalent</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Free</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">10 rewrites/day · 3 summaries/mo</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$0</div><div class="per">forever</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Casual users, light editing</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">—</div><div class="per">no free tier</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Advanced</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">30 rewrites/day · 15 summaries/mo</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$4.89</div><div class="per">per month (annual)</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Regular writers, students</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">$49</div><div class="per">starter · all-in</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Unlimited</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Unlimited rewrites + summaries</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$6.99</div><div class="per">per month (annual)</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Power users, professionals</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">$99</div><div class="per">pro · all-in</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-savings">
        <div class="big">Wordtune polishes your writing. theStacc publishes it.</div>
        <div class="lbl">Different tools — Wordtune is a writing aid, theStacc is a publishing engine.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-footnote">*Wordtune monthly billing: Advanced $6.99/mo, Unlimited $9.99/mo. 30% student discount with .edu email. 3-day free trial on paid plans. No refunds. Business plan priced custom.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Who it's for</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Who should buy Wordtune — <span class="accent">and who shouldn't.</span></h2>
      <p>The clearest filter: do you need to improve existing sentences, or create and publish new content?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Buy Wordtune if</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">You write and need sentence-level polish.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three signals Wordtune is the right fit.</p>
